    <section>
        <title>wrapper.syslog.facility</title>
        <para>
            Facility to use when logging to the syslog on UNIX systems.  Valid
            facility values include <literal moreinfo="none">USER</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL0</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL1</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL2</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL3</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL4</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL5</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL6</literal>, and
            <literal moreinfo="none">LOCAL7</literal>.  The default value is
            <literal moreinfo="none">USER</literal>.
        </para>
        <informalexample>
            <simpara><emphasis>Example:</emphasis></simpara>
            <screen format="linespecific"><![CDATA[wrapper.syslog.facility=USER]]></screen>
        </informalexample>
        <para>
            Custom facility values are used to set up things like remote
            logging, etc.
        </para>
    </section>
</chapter>
